Entry.Name: Statusword__Ready to operate
Entry.Comment:
- High in the initialization if mains voltage voltage between tolerances and dc link loaded. It allows the axis to be enabled.
- Low in operation, if mains voltage loss and dc link voltage undervoltage. It avoids the axis to be enabled again.

Entry.Name: Statusword__TorqueOFF order_n
Entry.Comment:
Low in operation by following errors: - Brake chopper failure - Device DC link over-voltage
Low in the initialization by following errors: - wrong config bits - eeprom read failure (invalid power pcb ids, device ids or factory settings) - loss parameters (default parameters and default factory settings not loaded) - brake resistor not found - wrong xml file or xml file still not checked - Parameter error

Entry.Name: Statusword__Brake ramp order_n
Entry.Comment: Low in operation by following errors: - Peak over current (device output side). It means a motoric load greater than 130%. - DC link overvoltage

Entry.Name: Statusword__Limit dc link current_order_n
Entry.Comment: Low in operation by following error: - Continuous over current (device output side). It means a motoric load greater than 102%.

Entry.Name: Statusword__NC handling_order_n
Entry.Comment: Low in operation by following errors: - Mains over-voltage: actual mains voltage above 20% or above mains voltage max tolerance (if greater than 20% parametrized). - Mains under-voltage: actual mains voltage below 30% or below mains voltage min tolerance (if greater than 30% parametrized). - Phase blackout (in 3-phases-mode) - Continuous over current (device output side). It means a motoric load greater than120%. - Excess temperature device. - Excess ambient temperature

Entry.Name: Warning__A2 PCB overtemperature
Entry.Comment: Actual pcb temperature above PCB temperature warning threshold (8000:0F). Code on display A0002
